                'title' => 'Fast Express Shipping Expands to 15 New Countries in Southeast Asia',
                'slug' => Str::slug('Fast Express Shipping Expands to 15 New Countries in Southeast Asia'),
                'excerpt' => 'Fast Express Shipping is proud to announce its expansion into 15 new countries across Southeast Asia, bringing reliable logistics to millions of new customers.',
                'body' => '<p>Fast Express Shipping has officially expanded its service network to include 15 new countries across Southeast Asia, a milestone that reflects our continued commitment to global logistics excellence. The newly added destinations include Vietnam, Cambodia, Laos, Myanmar, Brunei, and several Pacific island nations that have historically been underserved by major shipping providers.</p><p>This expansion comes after 18 months of strategic planning, infrastructure investment, and partnership development with local last-mile carriers. Our regional hub in Singapore now serves as the operational center for all Southeast Asian routes, enabling faster customs processing and reduced transit times for both business and personal shipments.</p><p>Businesses shipping to the region can expect transit times of 3–7 business days for Express service and 7–14 business days for Standard service. All shipments include real-time tracking, and dedicated customer support is available in English, Bahasa, Vietnamese, and Thai.</p><p>The Southeast Asian e-commerce market is projected to reach $300 billion by 2025, and our expanded presence positions Fast Express Shipping as the go-to logistics partner for businesses looking to tap into this growth. We have already onboarded over 200 new business clients in the first month of operation.</p><p>To celebrate the launch, we are offering a 15% discount on all first-time shipments to newly added destinations through the end of the quarter. Create your account today and take advantage of this introductory offer.</p>',
