                'title' => 'Holiday Shipping Deadlines 2024: Everything You Need to Know',
                'slug' => Str::slug('Holiday Shipping Deadlines 2024: Everything You Need to Know'),
                'excerpt' => 'Planning to ship gifts and packages this holiday season? Here are the key deadlines to ensure your shipments arrive on time for December 25th.',
                'body' => '<p>The holiday season is the busiest time of year for global logistics, and planning ahead is the best way to guarantee your packages arrive on time. Fast Express Shipping has compiled the key cutoff dates for the 2024 holiday season based on service level and destination region.</p><p>For domestic US shipments, the Standard service cutoff is December 15th, Express is December 20th, and Overnight is December 23rd for most major cities. For international shipments to Europe, Standard service must be submitted by December 10th, Express by December 17th. Shipments to Asia and Africa require even earlier submission — please check our holiday schedule page for country-specific deadlines.</p><p>Package volumes increase by up to 300% during the holiday period, and carrier networks experience significant strain. We strongly encourage all customers to ship as early as possible rather than relying on the final cutoff dates. Shipments submitted in early December have the highest probability of on-time delivery.</p><p>Packaging quality becomes even more important during peak season when packages are handled more frequently and quickly. Ensure all items are well-padded, boxes are securely sealed with reinforced tape, and fragile labels are prominently displayed. We offer complimentary packaging assessment at all Fast Express Shipping drop-off locations.</p><p>For business customers with high-volume holiday shipping needs, our dedicated business accounts team can arrange reserved capacity to guarantee your shipments are processed even during peak days. Contact your account manager or reach us at business@fastexpressshipping.com to arrange this service.</p>',
