            [
                'title' => '5 Common Packaging Mistakes That Lead to Damaged Shipments',
                'slug' => Str::slug('5 Common Packaging Mistakes That Lead to Damaged Shipments'),
                'excerpt' => 'Most shipment damage is preventable. Our logistics experts share the five most common packaging mistakes and exactly how to avoid them.',
                'body' => '<p>Despite advances in carrier handling technology, improper packaging remains the leading cause of shipment damage worldwide. Understanding what not to do is just as important as knowing best practices. Here are the five most common mistakes we see — and how to fix them.</p><p>The first mistake is using an undersized box. Many shippers reuse boxes that once held their items but have since weakened from prior use. A rule of thumb: if you can visibly see compression lines or creases in a box, retire it. Use a box with at least 5 cm of space on all sides for cushioning material. The second mistake is insufficient interior padding. Bubble wrap alone is often not enough for heavy items. For items over 2 kg, use a combination of bubble wrap around the item and foam inserts or packing peanuts to fill all void space. The item should not shift when you shake the sealed box.</p><p>The third mistake is improper sealing. Tape that runs only along the center seam of a box is inadequate. Use the H-taping method: run tape along all seams, including the center and both edges. Use pressure-sensitive tape at least 5 cm wide. The fourth mistake is packing incompatible items together. Liquids should never be packed with electronics or documents without secondary containment. Heavy items should not share a box with fragile ones without substantial separation.</p><p>The fifth and perhaps most overlooked mistake is failing to label correctly. "Fragile" labels matter — statistically, shipments with visible fragile markings are handled more carefully by sorting staff. Include a label inside the box as well, in case the outer label is damaged. Always include the destination address on an interior label as a redundancy measure.</p><p>Fast Express Shipping offers free packaging consultation at all drop-off locations. Our staff can assess your packaging before accepting the shipment and recommend improvements. We would rather spend two minutes helping you repack than process a damage claim later.</p>',
                'published_at' => Carbon::now()->subDays(58),
                'is_published' => true,
            ],
            [
                'title' => 'Introducing Overnight Delivery Service to Major African Cities',
                'slug' => Str::slug('Introducing Overnight Delivery Service to Major African Cities'),
                'excerpt' => 'Fast Express Shipping now offers Overnight delivery to Lagos, Nairobi, Johannesburg, Cairo, and Accra, bringing next-day logistics to Africa\'s fastest-growing business hubs.',
                'body' => '<p>Fast Express Shipping is delighted to announce the launch of Overnight delivery service to five major African cities: Lagos, Nigeria; Nairobi, Kenya; Johannesburg, South Africa; Cairo, Egypt; and Accra, Ghana. This service is available for shipments originating from the United States, United Kingdom, and the UAE, with additional origin cities being added in the coming months.</p><p>Overnight delivery to African destinations has historically been challenging due to limited direct flight capacity and complex last-mile infrastructure. We have overcome these challenges through partnerships with regional aviation partners and urban last-mile delivery networks in each target city. Shipments are loaded onto dedicated cargo holds on overnight flights and transferred to our local partners upon landing for same-morning delivery.</p><p>The service is ideal for businesses shipping time-sensitive documents, medical supplies, electronic components, and high-value goods to African markets. All Overnight shipments include GPS tracking, signature confirmation, and insurance coverage up to $2,500. Higher coverage is available upon request.</p><p>Pricing for Overnight service to Africa starts at $89 for documents under 0.5 kg and varies based on weight and declared value. Businesses shipping regularly to these cities can qualify for volume discounts through our Business Account program. Scheduled pickup is available, and drop-off is accepted at all Fast Express Shipping locations.</p><p>This launch reflects our belief that Africa represents one of the most important frontiers in global commerce. We are committed to expanding Overnight service to additional African cities throughout the year. Subscribe to our newsletter to be notified when new destinations are added.</p>',
                'published_at' => Carbon::now()->subDays(65),
