            [
                'title' => 'Important Changes to International Lithium Battery Shipping Regulations',
                'slug' => Str::slug('Important Changes to International Lithium Battery Shipping Regulations'),
                'excerpt' => 'Regulatory changes from IATA and ICAO now impose stricter requirements on shipping lithium batteries internationally. Here is what shippers need to know.',
                'body' => '<p>International air transport authorities including IATA and ICAO have implemented updated regulations for the shipment of lithium batteries, which take effect for all shipments processed after March 1, 2024. These changes affect anyone shipping smartphones, laptops, tablets, power banks, e-cigarettes, or any device containing a lithium-ion or lithium-metal battery.</p><p>The key changes include new state-of-charge requirements: lithium-ion batteries installed in devices must not exceed 30% charge when shipped as cargo. Standalone batteries (not installed in a device) must be packed in specific protective packaging with terminal protection and must not be shipped in quantities exceeding the per-package limits set by IATA. Lithium metal batteries, commonly found in cameras and medical devices, are now subject to even stricter quantity limits per package.</p><p>For most consumer electronics shipped in their original retail packaging, compliance is straightforward — original manufacturer packaging typically meets IATA requirements. The biggest change affects businesses shipping bulk quantities of batteries or replacement battery packs. These shipments now require a Shipper\'s Declaration for Dangerous Goods, which must be prepared by a trained and certified dangerous goods professional.</p><p>Fast Express Shipping has updated our online shipment submission form to flag shipments likely to contain lithium batteries and guide customers through the compliance requirements. Our staff at all drop-off locations are trained to identify non-compliant packaging and assist customers in meeting the new standards before accepting shipments.</p><p>Non-compliance with lithium battery regulations can result in shipment rejection at the origin airport, seizure at customs, and significant fines for the shipper. We take these regulations seriously for the safety of everyone in the supply chain. Contact our Dangerous Goods team at dg@fastexpressshipping.com if you have questions about specific battery-containing shipments.</p>',
                'published_at' => Carbon::now()->subDays(130),
                'is_published' => true,
            ],
            [
                'title' => 'Fast Express Shipping Launches Dedicated Healthcare Logistics Division',
                'slug' => Str::slug('Fast Express Shipping Launches Dedicated Healthcare Logistics Division'),
                'excerpt' => 'Our new Healthcare Logistics Division offers specialized shipping solutions for pharmaceuticals, medical devices, specimens, and temperature-sensitive healthcare products.',
                'body' => '<p>Fast Express Shipping has officially launched its Healthcare Logistics Division, a dedicated business unit focused on the unique demands of shipping pharmaceuticals, medical devices, biological specimens, and other healthcare-related products. This division operates under a separate quality management framework aligned with GDP (Good Distribution Practice) guidelines and applicable regional healthcare regulations.</p><p>The healthcare supply chain has zero tolerance for error. A delayed shipment of surgical instruments or temperature-compromised vaccines can have serious consequences. Our Healthcare Division addresses this through dedicated cold-chain corridors, temperature-monitored containers, and priority routing that keeps healthcare shipments ahead of general cargo at every facility.</p><p>Temperature control is a cornerstone of the Healthcare Division\'s capabilities. We offer three temperature range options: controlled room temperature (15–25°C), refrigerated (2–8°C), and frozen (-15 to -25°C). Real-time temperature monitoring is included for all healthcare shipments, with automatic alerts to our operations team if a temperature excursion is detected en route.</p><p>Our Healthcare Division clients include hospital procurement departments, pharmaceutical distributors, biotech companies, and clinical trial logistics coordinators. We provide customized shipping programs for recurring needs, including standing pickup schedules, dedicated account management, and monthly SLA performance reporting.</p><p>To inquire about healthcare logistics services, please contact our Healthcare Division team at healthcare@fastexpressshipping.com or call our dedicated line. We will conduct a free consultation to assess your specific needs and design a logistics program that meets your compliance and operational requirements.</p>',
                'published_at' => Carbon::now()->subDays(140),
