            [
                'title' => 'Guide to Prohibited and Restricted Items in International Shipping',
                'slug' => Str::slug('Guide to Prohibited and Restricted Items in International Shipping'),
                'excerpt' => 'Not everything can be shipped internationally. This guide covers the most commonly prohibited and restricted items and what to do if your goods fall into a gray area.',
                'body' => '<p>Every international shipping transaction is governed by a combination of airline regulations, national customs laws, and the policies of the shipping carrier. Understanding which items are prohibited or restricted is essential for every shipper — attempting to ship non-compliant goods can result in seizure, fines, and potential criminal liability.</p><p>Universally prohibited items include weapons, ammunition, explosives, narcotics and controlled substances, counterfeit goods, and goods that infringe intellectual property rights. These items cannot be shipped through any Fast Express Shipping service, and any attempt to do so will result in seizure and reporting to the appropriate authorities. No exceptions apply to this category.</p><p>Restricted items are goods that may be shipped but require special documentation, carrier approval, or compliance with specific packaging standards. This category includes lithium batteries (subject to IATA Dangerous Goods regulations), pharmaceuticals and controlled medicines (require export/import permits), perishable food items (subject to phytosanitary requirements), certain plants and seeds (subject to agricultural inspection), and high-value items like cash, jewelry, and precious metals (subject to declaration and insurance requirements).</p><p>Country-specific restrictions add another layer of complexity. Many countries prohibit or heavily restrict the import of certain food products, religious materials, or second-hand clothing. Some countries have strict import controls on electronics or require local certification of certain products. Fast Express Shipping\'s country guide, accessible from our website, lists the most significant country-specific restrictions for all destinations we serve.</p><p>If you are unsure whether your goods can be shipped, contact our compliance team before submitting your shipment. It is far better to ask in advance than to discover a problem after a shipment has been submitted. We review ambiguous cases promptly and can provide written guidance on whether and how a specific item can be shipped.</p>',
                'published_at' => Carbon::now()->subDays(220),
                'is_published' => true,
            ],
            [
                'title' => 'How to Prepare Your Business for Peak Shipping Season',
                'slug' => Str::slug('How to Prepare Your Business for Peak Shipping Season'),
                'excerpt' => 'Peak shipping season puts pressure on every part of the logistics chain. Here is how to prepare your business to handle high volumes without compromising delivery performance.',
                'body' => '<p>Peak shipping season — roughly October through January — is both the greatest opportunity and the greatest operational challenge for businesses that rely on shipping. Volume spikes can overwhelm unprepared operations, leading to delayed shipments, customer complaints, and lost revenue. The businesses that navigate peak season successfully are those that plan months in advance.</p><p>Inventory preparation is the foundation. Ensure your most popular products are stocked well before October. Supply chain disruptions during peak season are common, and running out of stock while demand is at its highest is a worst-case scenario. Coordinate with your suppliers in Q3 to confirm lead times and build buffer stock for your top-selling items.</p><p>On the logistics side, confirm your shipping agreements and capacity reservations with your carriers early. Fast Express Shipping offers capacity reservation for business customers who anticipate high volumes during peak season. This ensures your shipments are given priority processing even when overall volumes are elevated. Contact your account manager to discuss capacity options for this year\'s peak season.</p><p>Set accurate delivery expectation on your customer-facing platforms. Display shipping cutoff dates prominently on your website, in cart and checkout flows, and in marketing emails. Customers who receive realistic delivery estimates before purchasing are far less likely to become unhappy when their order takes a few days longer than usual due to peak season demand.</p><p>Finally, have a customer service plan ready. Even with perfect preparation, some shipments will experience delays during peak season. Empower your customer service team with accurate tracking information, a clear escalation path, and a framework for offering compensation when appropriate. A well-handled delay can preserve customer loyalty; a poorly-handled one can damage it permanently.</p>',
                'published_at' => Carbon::now()->subDays(240),
                'is_published' => true,
            ],
            [
                'title' => 'Understanding Delivery Exceptions: Causes and Solutions',
                'slug' => Str::slug('Understanding Delivery Exceptions: Causes and Solutions'),
                'excerpt' => 'A delivery exception means something unexpected happened with your shipment. Here is a breakdown of the most common causes and how Fast Express Shipping resolves them.',
                'body' => '<p>A "delivery exception" is a catch-all status that indicates something unexpected has occurred that may affect the scheduled delivery of a shipment. Exceptions are not the same as delivery failures — the vast majority are resolved within 24–48 hours without any action required from the shipper or recipient. Understanding what caused an exception helps set appropriate expectations.</p><p>Address-related exceptions are the most common. These occur when a delivery driver cannot locate the address as written, the address is incomplete, or there is a discrepancy between the address on the label and what the GPS system identifies. Prevention is straightforward: always double-check addresses before submitting a shipment, include apartment or suite numbers, and for international shipments, format the address according to the destination country\'s standard.</p><p>Weather-related exceptions are outside everyone\'s control. Extreme weather events — hurricanes, floods, blizzards, wildfires — can ground aircraft, close roads, and shut down sorting facilities. Fast Express Shipping proactively identifies weather-related disruptions and automatically adjusts estimated delivery dates for affected shipments. No action is typically required from customers during a weather exception.</p><p>Customs exceptions occur when additional documentation is required or when duties have not been paid. Our customs team monitors all international shipments and contacts the shipper immediately when a customs exception occurs. Providing the requested documentation promptly is the most effective way to resolve a customs hold quickly.</p><p>If you receive a delivery exception notification, first check the specific reason code in your tracking details. In most cases, the notification will include specific instructions. If you are unsure what to do or if the exception persists beyond 48 hours, contact our support team. We have direct relationships with all carrier partners and can often resolve exceptions more quickly than customers acting on their own.</p>',
                'published_at' => Carbon::now()->subDays(260),
                'is_published' => true,
            ],
            [
                'title' => 'Fast Express Shipping Introduces Real-Time SMS Notifications',
                'slug' => Str::slug('Fast Express Shipping Introduces Real-Time SMS Notifications'),
                'excerpt' => 'We have launched SMS tracking notifications, giving customers real-time shipment updates directly on their phones without needing to check email or the app.',
                'body' => '<p>Fast Express Shipping has launched real-time SMS notifications for all shipments, complementing our existing email and app-based tracking alerts. SMS notifications deliver key shipment milestones directly to the recipient\'s mobile phone, ensuring that tracking updates reach people even when they are not actively monitoring their inbox or app.</p><p>The notification system sends SMS alerts at four key milestones: when a shipment is picked up and enters the transit network, when it arrives in the destination country, when it is out for delivery, and when it is successfully delivered. For Express and Overnight shipments, an additional alert is sent when customs clearance is completed. Each SMS includes the tracking number, a brief status description, and a short link to the full tracking page.</p><p>Setting up SMS notifications is simple. During the shipment submission process, enter the recipient\'s mobile number in the "Notify SMS" field. Our system automatically sends alerts to that number throughout the shipment\'s journey. Senders can also opt in to receive copies of all SMS notifications at their own number, keeping them informed without needing to check the dashboard.</p><p>For business shippers, SMS notifications are included at no additional cost and can be enabled globally for all outgoing shipments in the Business Account settings. Custom notification workflows — for example, alerting a warehouse manager rather than the end customer at certain stages — are available through our API integration for businesses with custom logistics platforms.</p><p>SMS notification availability covers over 180 countries. If a recipient\'s number is not reachable by SMS in their country, the system automatically falls back to email notification. We are committed to ensuring every customer and recipient stays informed, regardless of how they prefer to communicate.</p>',
                'published_at' => Carbon::now()->subDays(280),
                'is_published' => true,
            ],
            [
                'title' => 'The Complete Guide to Shipping Electronics Internationally',
                'slug' => Str::slug('The Complete Guide to Shipping Electronics Internationally'),
                'excerpt' => 'Electronics require special care, correct documentation, and compliance with international regulations. This comprehensive guide covers everything you need to know.',
                'body' => '<p>Electronics are among the most commonly shipped and most commonly damaged items in international logistics. The combination of sensitivity to static, temperature extremes, and physical shock makes proper preparation essential. Beyond the physical handling concerns, electronics also come with a set of regulatory and customs considerations that every international shipper should understand.</p><p>Before packing, identify whether your electronics contain lithium batteries. As covered in our earlier guide on battery regulations, lithium-containing devices are subject to IATA Dangerous Goods regulations for air transport. Ensure batteries are charged to no more than 30% for cargo shipments, are protected against short circuits, and are packed in compliant packaging. Non-compliance can result in shipment rejection or, in serious cases, fire risk.</p><p>For packing, use anti-static bubble wrap (the pink variety) for sensitive components such as circuit boards, hard drives, and RAM modules. Standard clear bubble wrap creates static electricity that can damage electronic components. Use rigid outer packaging — not envelopes or padded mailers — for any electronic device. Fill all void space with foam or inflated air pillows. A device should not rattle or shift inside the box.</p><p>For customs purposes, electronics typically fall under HS Chapter 84 or 85. The declared value must reflect the replacement cost of the item in the destination country, not the price you paid for it. Many countries apply significant import duties to electronics — rates of 15–25% are common in parts of Asia and Africa. Our duties estimator will help you calculate the likely import cost before you ship.</p><p>Used or refurbished electronics may require additional documentation in some countries, including proof of testing and a certificate of conformity. Some countries require electronics to carry local safety certification marks (like CE in Europe or FCC in the US) to be imported. Our compliance team can advise on country-specific requirements for specific electronics categories. Contact us before shipping high-value electronics internationally to ensure a smooth, compliant delivery.</p>',
                'published_at' => Carbon::now()->subDays(300),
                'is_published' => true,
            ],
            [
                'title' => 'How We Ensure the Safety of High-Value Shipments',
                'slug' => Str::slug('How We Ensure the Safety of High-Value Shipments'),
                'excerpt' => 'High-value shipments require more than standard logistics procedures. Learn about the multi-layered security protocols Fast Express Shipping uses to protect precious cargo.',
                'body' => '<p>Shipping high-value goods — fine jewelry, luxury watches, cash equivalents, artwork, precious metals, or high-end electronics — is a fundamentally different proposition from shipping everyday items. The risk profile is higher, the consequences of loss or theft are greater, and the required security measures are substantially more rigorous. Fast Express Shipping has developed a comprehensive high-value shipment program to meet these demands.</p><p>The first layer of protection is confidentiality. High-value shipments are labeled and documented in a way that does not reveal the contents to anyone handling the package. Instead of "Diamond Jewelry" on the contents declaration, our system uses coded descriptions that indicate the item category to our customs team but not to general handling staff. Plain, unmarked outer packaging is used to eliminate visual cues that might attract attention.</p><p>For shipments over $5,000, we require shipment through our dedicated high-value channel. These shipments travel in separate, locked containers within carrier vehicles, are transferred between facilities with chain-of-custody documentation, and require supervisor sign-off at each facility checkpoint. The number of individuals who have physical access to high-value containers is minimized throughout the journey.</p><p>Insurance is mandatory for high-value shipments. Our high-value insurance program, underwritten by a Lloyd\'s of London syndicate, covers loss and damage at declared value for items up to $50,000. For items exceeding this threshold, we can arrange specialist coverage on a case-by-case basis. Our claims process for high-value items is handled by a dedicated team and typically resolves within 10 business days.</p><p>Signature confirmation and identity verification are required for all high-value deliveries. Recipients must present government-issued photo ID, which is recorded by the delivery agent. Delivery to unattended locations or alternate recipients is not permitted without prior written authorization from the shipper. Contact our High-Value Logistics team to arrange a shipment or discuss a specific requirement.</p>',
                'published_at' => Carbon::now()->subDays(330),
                'is_published' => true,
            ],
            [
                'title' => 'Fast Express Shipping\'s New Mobile App: Ship on the Go',
                'slug' => Str::slug('Fast Express Shippings New Mobile App Ship on the Go'),
                'excerpt' => 'Our new mobile app brings the full power of Fast Express Shipping to your smartphone, letting you create shipments, track packages, and manage your account anywhere.',
                'body' => '<p>Fast Express Shipping\'s new mobile application is now available for download on both iOS and Android. The app brings the full functionality of our web platform to your smartphone, enabling you to manage your shipping needs from anywhere in the world. Whether you are at a warehouse, trade show, or on the road, the app keeps your logistics under control.</p><p>The core feature of the app is the streamlined shipment creation flow. We have redesigned the form specifically for mobile input, with smart address auto-complete, saved address books, and the ability to photograph documents and package labels directly from the app. Creating a new shipment takes under two minutes for returning customers with saved preferences.</p><p>Tracking is prominently featured on the app\'s home screen. All active shipments display in a real-time list with color-coded status indicators, so you can see at a glance which shipments are on track and which may need attention. Tapping any shipment opens the full tracking timeline with map visualization and estimated delivery time.</p><p>Business account features are fully supported in the app, including multi-shipment batch management, team member access for business accounts with multiple users, invoice and receipt downloading, and real-time analytics summaries. Notifications are delivered as push alerts, meaning you are informed of key updates even when the app is not actively open.</p><p>The app also includes a cryptocurrency payment module that generates QR codes for payment directly within the app, making it simple to submit crypto payments from a mobile wallet. We will continue releasing updates throughout the year to add new features based on customer feedback. Download Fast Express Shipping from the App Store or Google Play today and leave us a review to help us improve.</p>',
                'published_at' => Carbon::now()->subDays(365),
                'is_published' => true,
